/7aM%_yFnTqyN|C(shG--warrior-dialogue-li: warrior-dialogue
I feel very proud of my Warrior name.
Occasionally, I used to think about how my name would sound with "star" at the end of it... you know, for curiosity's sake.
Sometimes it's hard to know exactly what loyalty means.
I sometimes wonder if it's most important to be loyal to the Warrior Code, or the ones you love.. Obviously, I hope those are always the same thing, but if they aren't...
I know someone who fell in love with a cat from another Clan.
You never fully know another cat's secrets
Sometimes the past echoes in the present.
I wish I could see into the future.
I've been going on a lot of patrols recently.
I like exploring the forest.
The dappled light in the forest is beautiful.
I feel very protected underneath a canopy of leaves.
I bet all the apprentices wish they could sleep in the Warriors den.
I remember being a young Warrior... so full of dreams!
The life of a Warrior is full of hard work.
I hope you've been going on plenty of patrols recently.
It's very important to explore the forest.
I hope there are plenty of herbs in the medicine cat den.
It's always sad when a leader steps down.
It's hard to keep track of everything all the time.
I'm trying to balance a lot of things.
I have faith that StarClan will guide us well.
I remember when I was a kit and wanted to be a great Warrior one day.
Being a leader comes with great responsibility.
I wonder what our ancestors are thinking.
I hope I'm doing enough to help my Clan.
We all work hard in this Clan.
I'm proud to come home to our camp.
I like my den a lot. It's cozy and pretty.
I do think the medicine cat's den is one of the prettiest.
I love the waterfall in the medicine cat's den.
Whenever I'm in the medicine cat's den, it's very soothing.
It's really important for a Clan to feel protected by their medicine cat.
Of course, no medicine cat is expected to know everything.
It would be impossible for a single cat to know every remedy.
Some cats are really good at recognizing herbs.
I love wandering through the forest.
The forest is especially pretty these days.
I find the trees around us so beautiful.
I love all the plants around here.
Great StarClan, I'm hungry.
I could really go for a mouse-tail right now.
I'd really like to chow down on some vole.
Rabbit is a delicacy, and I'm craving it.
It's been a long time since I've eaten a squirrel.
I wish I could eat a tasty bird right about now.
You ever get hungry when you're out on patrol? I sure do.
I always thank StarClan for my kill when I go hunting.
It took me a long time to learn how to hunt well.
I feel like I'm always learning how to hunt better.
Every time I search for herbs, I think I get better at it.
Some herbs are very hard to recognize.
Some herbs look exactly like other herbs.
I've always known how to find cobwebs. That's an easy one.
When I was an apprentice, I was always off fetching cobwebs.
Looking back, apprentice tasks were kind of fun.
It was fun being an apprentice and trying to be helpful all the time.
When I was an apprentice... let's just say I didn't always succeed at being helpful.
I was... occasionally a troublemaker when I was younger.
I have to admit, I used to love pulling pranks.
I'm too mature to play pranks... most of the time.
Occasionally I like to play a little prank on one of my fellow Clan members.
No harm in a little fun prank
I would never prank anyone in a mean way.
When I was an apprentice, some of the pranks I played on other apprentices were... a little over-the-top.
I've changed a lot as I've grown older.
I'm not as reckless as I used to be.
I wonder what StarClan thinks of forbidden love.
Sometimes I wonder why medicine cats aren't allowed to fall in love.
I trust the Warrior Code completely.
I like the path I chose in life.
When I go to Gatherings, I'm proud to represent our Clan.
I love our Clan a lot.
When I was a kit, I idolized our Clan's leader.
It's natural to look up to those who are older than you.
Respect for elders is very, very important.
Elders and queens must always be treated with great respect.
The elders' den and the nursery are very important places.
As a kit, I was so eager to leave the nursery.
When I was young, I looked up to the Warriors in our Clan so much.
Becoming a Warrior was one of the best days of my life.
Becoming an apprentice was a very exciting day
I'll never forget how excited I was when I received my Warrior name.
When I became a Warrior, I was hoping my leader would choose a good name for me... and they did!
Warrior ceremonies are so exciting.
Apprentice ceremonies are pretty fun.
It's always wonderful when new kits are born.
I'm always excited when it's time for a ceremony.
I'm glad that we've had a lot of prey recently.
I feel pretty optimistic about the cold moons ahead.
We have a lot of Warriors who are very skilled.
We train good Warriors in this Clan.
The Warriors in this Clan work very hard.
I love belonging to this Clan.
This camp is very comfortable and sheltered.
Recently, our fresh-kill pile has been very plentiful.
I ought to swing by the medicine cat's den.
It's important that we keep our supplies of herbs well-stocked.
We have a pretty good amount of herbs in storage, but we could always use more.
There's no such thing as being too prepared.
StarClan has smiled on us recently
I'm starving. Is it time to eat yet?
There are a lot of things I want to do today.
I like walking around our Camp and talking to everyone.
It's nice to hear how other cats in the Clan are doing.
Everyone in the Clan has their duties, and everyone knows their role.
I used to dream of being leader when I was very small.
Have you been to the forest recently?
Collecting herbs is very enjoyable.
Hunting is a lot of fun.
I really enjoy walking through the forest.
The leader's den is a very calm and quiet place.
The medicine cat's den is one of my favorite places to be.
Great StarClan, I love the pool in the medicine cat's den!
When I listen to the sound of rushing water, I feel calmed.
I love the way water looks under the moonlight.
The other day I was sure I saw a cat trying to attack me from inside a pool! ... Turns out it was my reflection.
Hey, we all make mistakes sometimes.
Pobody's nerfect.
Nobody's perfect.
Nobody's purr-fect.
The leaves haven't started changing yet, so greenleaf should last a while.
I have to say, I'm worried for leaf-bare.
Do you think it's true that this coming leaf-bare is going to be one of the coldest?
I've been hunting as much as I can. I hope it's enough.
The warm weather is only going to last so long.
We have to prepare for the cold moons that may lie ahead.
Greenleaf is beautiful. It reminds me of being a kit.
I used to love playing with yarn. It's been a while since I took the time to play.
I remember the games I used to play with my littermates. We had so much fun.
When I was a kit, my siblings and I always used to fight over who got to sleep in "The Comfy Spot" in the nursery. Great StarClan, we were so young!
My mother always used to tell me stories about the great Warriors in my family line.
My grandmother was a rogue who joined this Clan. She didn't understand Clan life at first, but came to love it.
Rogues may think our customs are strange, but there's a reason behind everything in the Warrior Code.
When I was an apprentice, I'll admit... I made fun of the Warrior Code from time to time.
Now that I'm a Warrior, I respect the Warrior Code deeply.
I remember the day I became a Warrior like it was yesterday.
I was so proud to stand a vigil for the first time.
Great StarClan, I was so competitive when I was an apprentice!
When I was younger, I wanted to be the best in everything! The crazy things I used to say...
I'll bet I can catch more mice than you today!
No doubt about it, I'm the best vole-hunter around.
I almost caught a bird once, but, uh... it made an escape in the upwards direction. Next time, I'll get one. Next time.
I bet you I could catch a rabbit if the weather was right!
When I was a kit, I thought a lot about being a medicine cat.
It's important for a medicine cat to provide for their Clan and keep everyone safe.
I always like helping to collect medicine cat herbs... although sometimes I can't tell them apart.
Sometimes, all the medicine cat herbs just look like leaves to me.
Have you had any visions from StarClan recently?
I'd like to have a vision from StarClan sometime. I know they don't visit everyone
My grandfather runs with StarClan. When I look up at the stars at night, I almost feel like I can see him.
I'm not scared of the dark, not even a little bit! Well, um, actually... okay, yes, maybe a little bit. Okay, maybe a lot. What were we talking about?
It's perfectly normal to be afraid of things. When I was an apprentice, I was scared of the Carrionplace. And now... oh, wait, I'm still scared of the Carrionplace.
Have you seen any Twolegs recently?
Thankfully, I haven't seen any Twolegs near our camp in a long time.
Our camp is very well-fortified and safe. It puts me at ease.
Remember when that group of rogues attacked a few moons ago? I'm glad we were able to drive them out.
I don't look forward to battles or anything, but... they are pretty exciting.
It's good to keep my combat skills sharp.
I think it's important for apprentices to spend some time with all of the senior Warriors. It helps them learn respect and responsibility.
Training apprentices is a very important thing.
It makes a lot of sense that generally, a Warrior has to have trained an apprentice before they can become deputy.
I remember many, many moons ago, a Warrior named Briartail became deputy even though he hadn't trained an apprentice. It took the Clan some time to get used to it.
The Warrior Code is very important.
At the end of the day, one must trust their leader's judgment over everything else.
It's important to know your role as a Warrior, and truly understand what your duties are.
No one should make decisions for the Clan alone.
Sure, everyone thinks they can be leader. Doesn't mean everyone can be.
Have you visited the nursery today?
Even though I have to be serious most of the time, I have to admit... kits are pretty cute.
It's nice to see young cats who are free-spirited and playful.
I was definitely very, uh, playful when I was a kit. May or may not have gotten into quite a bit of mischief.
I was a bit of a rascal when I was still with my mother in the nursery.
I remember when I was a kit, I would sometimes try to attach burrs to the pelts of senior Warriors... got myself into quite a bit of trouble.
My mother always used to scold me for running around the camp and getting into everyone's business.
When you're a kit, you just want to see everything and do everything. It's natural!
As you grow up, you take on more responsibility and respect for the ways of the Clan.
I spend a lot of time thinking about how I can protect this Clan.
It's always fun getting to go to a Gathering.
I enjoy Gatherings a lot.
It's nice to hear about how other Clans are doing.
Do you have any friends in other Clans?
I have some friends across the river.
I like meeting cats from other Clans at Fourtrees.
Even though we're four different Clans, we all inhabit the same forest and live by the same code.
All four Clans obey the Warrior Code... at least, our neighboring Clans obey it most of the time. *cough* *cough*
If I had to live in another Clan, I don't know which one I'd choose.
The only Clan I'd want to live in is ours. I feel very proud to belong to it.
I wonder if any kits will be born soon?
It's always nice to see litters of young kits scurrying around.
I've always thought that names starting with "Ash" were very pretty.
Can I say an unpopular opinion? I used to think the best part about being a leader would be getting to choose everyone's Warrior names.
When I was young, I thought I'd choose really good Warrior names if I was leader. Just saying.
To be honest, if I had chosen everyone's Warrior names when I was young, I would have made them all end in "heart," because "heart" sounds cool.
/7aM%_yFnTqyN|C(shG--apprentice-dialogue: apprentice-dialogue
I want to receive my Warrior name already!
I admire our leader so much.
Have you gone hunting recently?
I love hunting.
Catching mice is easy.
Catching voles is kind of hard.
I'm the best around when it comes to catching shrews.
I want to eat with the senior warriors tonight!
I hope all the apprentices look up to me one day!
I'll race you to the forest!
Want to go on patrol?
I wanna hunt!
I love the forest.
Exploring is awesome!
Let's race!
Our medicine cat is so cool.
If I get an injury I know our medicine cat will heal me!
I'd like to be deputy!
The deputy is awesome.
It must be hard to be a Warrior.
I want to help this Clan a lot!
I bet I could win a hunting competition!
I never want to become an Elder! I want to be busy all day every day!
I'm gonna be the next leader! Believe it!
Want to see who can collect more herbs?
One time I almost got lost in the forest!
I'm not scared of anything.
I'm not even scared of rogues. Or Twolegs!
I've never seen a Twoleg before.
Twolegs must be really weird!
I wanna fulfill my duty to my Clan!
I'm gonna be the best apprentice ever!
Just you wait, I'm gonna be the best Warrior of all time!
I wanna be a leader so I can have nine lives.
Being a leader sounds like so much fun.
I want to rule this Clan!
If I was leader and you bothered me, I'd banish ya!
I hope I get to go to the next Gathering.
Gatherings sound like so much fun.
Have you ever caught a rabbit?
I've never caught a rabbit but I want to.
I bet I've caught a million mice!
/7aM%_yFnTqyN|C(shG--kit-dialogue-list: I can't wait to be a great Warrior one day!

I like playing with other kits.
I wanna be deputy and medicine cat!
I want to have an apprentice!
The apprentices are all so big...

I've never been inside the leader's den...
I wonder what the Warriors' den is like!
